        "summary": "Anchovy Crostini With Onion-and-raisin Relish might be just the <b>Mediterranean</b> recipe you are searching for. This dairy free and pescatarian recipe serves 6 and costs <b>$3.04 per serving</b>. This hor d'oeuvre has <b>441 calories</b>, <b>16g of protein</b>, and <b>15g of fat</b> per serving. Not a lot of people made this recipe, and 1 would say it hit the spot. If you have baguette, wine, oil-packed white-anchovy, and a few other ingredients on hand, you can make it. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes roughly <b>45 minutes</b>. It is brought to you by Martha Stewart. With a spoonacular <b>score of 77%</b>, this dish is solid. Similar recipes include <a href=\"https://spoonacular.com/recipes/picnic-crostini-with-roasted-pepper-onion-and-anchovy-309522\">Picnic Crostini with Roasted Pepper, Onion, and Anchovy</a>, <a href=\"https://spoonacular.com/recipes/herb-crostini-with-blue-cheese-spread-and-caramelized-onion-relish-223287\">Herb Crostini with Blue Cheese Spread and Caramelized Onion Relish</a>, and <a href=\"https://spoonacular.com/recipes/egg-and-anchovy-crostini-66\">Egg and Anchovy Crostini</a>.",
