        "summary": "If you have about <b>45 minutes</b> to spend in the kitchen, Hard-Cooked Eggs with Crisp Anchovy Crumbs might be an outstanding <b>pescatarian</b> recipe to try. This recipe makes 20 servings with <b>77 calories</b>, <b>4g of protein</b>, and <b>5g of fat</b> each. For <b>21 cents per serving</b>, this recipe <b>covers 4%</b> of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. Not a lot of people made this recipe, and 1 would say it hit the spot. It is brought to you by Food and Wine. If you have anchovy fillets, lemon zest, butter, and a few other ingredients on hand, you can make it. It works well as an inexpensive hor d'oeuvre. Overall, this recipe earns a <b>not so excellent spoonacular score of 13%</b>. Users who liked this recipe also liked <a href=\"https://spoonacular.com/recipes/hard-cooked-eggs-with-radishes-and-anchovy-butter-crostini-84875\">Hard-Cooked Eggs with Radishes and Anchovy-Butter Crostini</a>, <a href=\"https://spoonacular.com/recipes/farfalle-pasta-with-cauliflower-anchovy-and-hard-cooked-egg-491922\">Farfalle Pasta With Cauliflower, Anchovy And Hard-Cooked Egg</a>, and <a href=\"https://spoonacular.com/recipes/hard-cooked-eggs-with-herb-mayonnaise-44506\">Hard-cooked Eggs With Herb Mayonnaise</a>.",
