        "summary": "Tomato-and-Anchovy Salad with Garlic Cream is a <b>gluten free, primal, and pescatarian</b> hor d'oeuvre. This recipe serves 4. One serving contains <b>194 calories</b>, <b>5g of protein</b>, and <b>15g of fat</b>. For <b>$2.6 per serving</b>, this recipe <b>covers 12%</b> of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. Not a lot of people made this recipe, and 1 would say it hit the spot. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes roughly <b>30 minutes</b>. Head to the store and pick up aged balsamic vinegar, garlic cloves, basil leaves, and a few other things to make it today. It is brought to you by Food and Wine. Overall, this recipe earns a <b>pretty good spoonacular score of 69%</b>. Similar recipes include <a href=\"https://spoonacular.com/recipes/pappardelle-with-tomato-garlic-and-anchovy-sauce-365697\">Pappardelle with Tomato, Garlic and Anchovy Sauce</a>, <a href=\"https://spoonacular.com/recipes/anchovy-little-gem-and-tomato-salad-53\">Anchovy, Little Gem, And Tomato Salad</a>, and <a href=\"https://spoonacular.com/recipes/anchovy-cherry-tomato-salad-695641\">Anchovy & Cherry Tomato Salad</a>.",
