        "summary": "If you have roughly <b>1 hour and 10 minutes</b> to spend in the kitchen, Alex's Anchovy Bucatini might be an outstanding <b>pescatarian</b> recipe to try. This recipe makes 4 servings with <b>923 calories</b>, <b>30g of protein</b>, and <b>43g of fat</b> each. For <b>$3.21 per serving</b>, this recipe <b>covers 29%</b> of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. It works well as a pretty expensive main course. 1 person has made this recipe and would make it again. It is brought to you by Foodnetwork. If you have bread, anchovy fillets, olive oil, and a few other ingredients on hand, you can make it. Overall, this recipe earns a <b>pretty good spoonacular score of 58%</b>. If you like this recipe, take a look at these similar recipes: <a href=\"https://spoonacular.com/recipes/dinner-tonight-bucatini-con-salsicce-bucatini-with-sausage-208324\">Dinner Tonight: Bucatini con Salsicce (Bucatini with Sausage)</a>, <a href=\"https://spoonacular.com/recipes/bucatini-with-skate-sauce-bucatini-alla-razza-323852\">Bucatini with Skate Sauce: Bucatini alla Razza</a>, and <a href=\"https://spoonacular.com/recipes/bucatini-with-spicy-tomato-sauce-bucatini-allamatriciana-77151\">Bucatini With Spicy Tomato Sauce (bucatini All'amatriciana)</a>.",
